  deepcli agent list|show [args] [--json] [--output path]
                                   Inspect sub-agent task descriptors
  deepcli test [discover|run] [--json] [--output path]
                                   Discover or run project tests
  deepcli env check|plan|setup|install|test [args] [--json] [--output path]
                                   Check, plan, set up, or verify local task environments
  deepcli check [docker|compiler] [--json]
                                   Shortcut for environment readiness check
  deepcli docker|compiler [check|plan|setup|install|test] [--json]
                                   Target-first local environment workflow
  deepcli setup [docker|compiler] [--smoke]
                                   Shortcut for environment setup
  deepcli install [docker|compiler] [--smoke]
                                   Alias for environment install/setup
  deepcli diagnose [--limit n] [--bundle dir]
                                   Run a fast workspace + session diagnosis
  deepcli support [bundle-dir]    Create a redacted support bundle and issue draft
  deepcli init [--quick]          Run /init without typing the slash
  deepcli status|usage|next|goal|plan|fork|accept|gate|verify|handoff|trace|logs|privacy|recipes|scorecard|benchmark|round|selftest|preflight|completion
                                   Run common diagnostic slash commands
  deepcli tui                     Start the terminal UI in the current directory
  deepcli ask <prompt>            Run a one-shot task in the current directory
  deepcli stream <prompt>         Run a streaming one-shot chat task
  deepcli kimi [ask|stream|resume|tui|repl|version|about|diagnose|support|health|timeout|model|provider|use|switch|models|providers|goal|plan|fork|history|cleanup|accept|gate|login|logout|check|docker|compiler|setup|logs|privacy|recipes|scorecard|benchmark|round|selftest|preflight|completion] [args...]
                                   Use --provider kimi --model kimi-for-coding
  deepcli deepseek [ask|stream|resume|tui|repl|version|about|diagnose|support|health|timeout|model|provider|use|switch|models|providers|goal|plan|fork|history|cleanup|accept|gate|login|logout|check|docker|compiler|setup|logs|privacy|recipes|scorecard|benchmark|round|selftest|preflight|completion] [args...]
                                   Use --provider deepseek --model deepseek-v4-pro
  deepcli help                    Show this help

All other arguments are forwarded to the binary. The wrapper adds defaults unless
you supplied them:
  -C "$PWD" --config "$DEEPCLI_CONFIG" --yes

Examples:
  deepcli
  deepcli repl
  deepcli tui
  deepcli resume
  deepcli quickstart
  deepcli quickstart --json --output .deepcli/exports/quickstart.json
  deepcli quickstart --json --fail-on-missing
